casebody.data:
Alexander HURSH et al., Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6756. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 15, 1932. H. L. Arterberry, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Samuel W. McNabb, U. S. Atty., and P. V. Davis, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal dismissed for failure of appellants to file record and docket cause.
